# Subset data for Early Summer Model
data_early <- dplyr::select(data, Year, EarlySummerAnoxicVol, JanAprTNLoad, JanMayTNLoad, MayFlow, MSL, windfrc) %>% filter(if_all(c(EarlySummerAnoxicVol, JanAprTNLoad, JanMayTNLoad, MayFlow, MSL, windfrc), ~ !is.na(.)))
model_early_full <- lm(EarlySummerAnoxicVol ~ JanAprTNLoad + JanMayTNLoad + MayFlow + MSL + windfrc, data = data_early)
model_early <- stepAIC(model_early_full, direction = "both", trace = TRUE)

# Generate the equivalent equations from the model in paper-like format
format_equation <- function(model, label) {
  coefs <- coef(model)
  eq <- paste0(
    "\u0177_{", label, "} = ", 
    sprintf("%.3f", coefs[1]), 
    paste(sprintf(" + %.3f %s", coefs[-1], names(coefs)[-1]), collapse = "")
  )
  return(eq)
}

# Residual plots
data_early$residuals_early <- residuals(model_early)
data_late$residuals_late <- residuals(model_late)

plot_early_resid <- ggplot(data_early, aes(x = Year, y = residuals_early)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "red") +
  labs(title = "Residuals: Early Summer", y = "Residuals") +

        axis.title = element_text(size = 8))

### Step 5: Bootstrap for P-Values (Table 2 CART Values)
# Define a statistic function for bootstrap
boot_stat_early <- function(data, indices) {
  d <- data[indices, ]
  tree <- rpart(residuals_early ~ Year, data = d, control = rpart.control(minbucket = 4, maxdepth = 2))
  return(tree$cptable[which.min(tree$cptable[, "xerror"]), "CP"])
}

set.seed(123)
boot_early <- boot(data = data_early, statistic = boot_stat_early, R = 1000)
cat("Early Summer CART Bootstrapped p-value:", mean(boot_early$t), "\n")
Early Summer CART Bootstrapped p-value: 0.06727018

  d <- data[indices, ]
  tree <- rpart(residuals_late ~ Year, data = d, control = rpart.control(minbucket = 4, maxdepth = 2))
  return(tree$cptable[which.min(tree$cptable[, "xerror"]), "CP"])
}

set.seed(123)
boot_late <- boot(data = data_late, statistic = boot_stat_late, R = 1000)
